# Implementation Plan - Mission 4.7: GitHub Pages Alignment

This plan outlines the steps to align the repository for GitHub Pages deployment by moving the production build output to the project root.

## Proposed Changes

### Build Alignment

The production build has already been generated via `npm run build` and is located in the `dist/` directory. For GitHub Pages to serve the site correctly from the root, we must move these files to the repository root.

> [!WARNING]
> This operation will overwrite the source code `index.html` in the project root with the minified production version. This is required for GitHub Pages integration but means the repository will now serve as a deployment branch.

#### [MODIFY] Project Root
- Move all files from `dist/` to `./`.
- This includes `index.html`, `assets/`, and any other build artifacts.

### Git Operations
- Stage the changes.
- Commit with: `"Deployment: Aligning build files for GitHub Pages root"`.
- Push to the remote origin.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Verify that `index.html` in the root now contains references to the bundled assets (e.g., `/Unplug/assets/...`).
- Verify that the `assets/` folder exists in the root and contains the JS/CSS bundles.
- Check the git status and log to ensure the commit was successful.
